abstract: U.S. special envoy for North Korea, Stephen Biegun, urged Pyongyang on Monday to return offers of talks, dismissing leader Kim Jong Un's year-end deadline while highlighting Washington's willingness to discuss "all issues of interest".

lead_paragraph: SEOUL — U.S. special envoy for North Korea, Stephen Biegun, urged Pyongyang on Monday to return offers of talks, dismissing leader Kim Jong Un's year-end deadline while highlighting Washington's willingness to discuss "all issues of interest".
headline_main: U.S. Envoy Biegun to North Korea: 'We're Here, You Know How to Reach Us'

abstract: Kamaru Usman sent a bloodied, bleary Colby Covington spiraling to the ground for the second time. Usman then leaped on him and went to work on Covington's badly injured face, battering his dazed opponent with hammer fists until the referee mercifully intervened.
snippet: Kamaru Usman sent a bloodied, bleary Colby Covington spiraling to the ground for the second time. Usman then leaped on him and went to work on Covington's badly injured face, battering his dazed opponent with hammer fists until the referee mercifu...
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Kamaru Usman sent a bloodied, bleary Colby Covington spiraling to the ground for the second time. Usman then leaped on him and went to work on Covington's badly injured face, battering his dazed opponent with hammer fists until the referee mercifully intervened.
headline_main: Usman Batters Covington, Volkanovski Claims Title at UFC 245
headline_print_headline: Usman Batters Covington, Volkanovski Claims Title at UFC 245

abstract: Iran's telecommunications minister announced on Sunday that the country has defused a second cyberattack in less than a week, this time “aimed at spying on government intelligence."

lead_paragraph: TEHRAN, Iran — Iran's telecommunications minister announced on Sunday that the country has defused a second cyberattack in less than a week, this time “aimed at spying on government intelligence."
headline_main: Iran Says It's Defused 2nd Cyberattack in Less Than a Week
headline_print_headline: Iran Says It's Defused 2nd Cyberattack in Less Than a Week

abstract: In a story Dec. 13, 2019, about the Supreme Court agreeing to hear President Donald Trump’s pleas to keep his tax, bank and financial records private, The Associated Press erroneously reported in some versions that Trump had stated during the 2016 campaign that he couldn’t be prosecuted or investigated as president even if he were to shoot someone on New York’s Fifth Avenue.
snippet: In a story Dec. 13, 2019, about the Supreme Court agreeing to hear President Donald Trump’s pleas to keep his tax, bank and financial records private, The Associated Press erroneously reported in some versions that Trump had stated during the 2016...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In a story Dec. 13, 2019, about the Supreme Court agreeing to hear President Donald Trump’s pleas to keep his tax, bank and financial records private, The Associated Press erroneously reported in some versions that Trump had stated during the 2016 campaign that he couldn’t be prosecuted or investigated as president even if he were to shoot someone on New York’s Fifth Avenue.

abstract: Quotation of the Day for Sunday, December 15, 2019.
snippet: Quotation of the Day for Sunday, December 15, 2019.
lead_paragraph: “There’s something about the ongoing saga of President Trump that hasn’t gone away. This isn’t an event so much as an ongoing occurrence, something that feels life-changing, something that has changed the country in ways that has implications for the way that people live.”
headline_main: Quotation of the Day: As Impeachment and 2020 Loom, Democrats Unite in Worry

abstract: Three of the four Heisman finalists, including Louisiana State’s Burrow, transferred to their current teams from other schools.
snippet: Three of the four Heisman finalists, including Louisiana State’s Burrow, transferred to their current teams from other schools.
lead_paragraph: If the three quarterbacks who arrived in New York as finalists for the Heisman Trophy — Jalen Hurts of Oklahoma, Justin Fields of Ohio State and Joe Burrow of Louisiana State — harbored this dream when they set off for college, the reality came in a different hue.

abstract: A Department of Defense memo issued last month allows athletes who play for military academies to seek to delay their service obligations if they pursue professional sports.
snippet: A Department of Defense memo issued last month allows athletes who play for military academies to seek to delay their service obligations if they pursue professional sports.
lead_paragraph: While military service academies have long competed in college sports, they have mostly emphasized training future officers rather than serving as a steppingstone for athletes seeking a career in professional leagues.

abstract: A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
snippet: A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
headline_main: Democrat Lawmaker Opposed to Impeachment Will Switch Parties: Report
headline_print_headline: Democrat Lawmaker Opposed to Impeachment Will Switch Parties: Report
